sql:
SELECT AVG(popularity) AS Average_Popularity
FROM films
WHERE director_name = 'Christopher Nolan';

external_knowledge:
- "Majestic voyages of cinema" metaphorically refers to films;
- "Sailed beyond the two-hour mark" refers to a runtime of more than 120 minutes;
- "Dawn of the new millennium" refers to the year 2000 and beyond;
- "Embraced by at least fifty critics on IMDb" indicates a minimum of 50 IMDb votes;
- "Earning more than ten million in the global market" refers to a box office revenue exceeding $10,000,000;
- "Average critique" refers to the average user rating;
- "Voices who have voiced their opinions" refers to the number of reviewers;
- "Average IMDb score" refers to the average rating given by IMDb voters.

sql:
SELECT f.original_title, ur.review
FROM films f
JOIN user_ratings ur ON f.film_id = ur.film_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Home gardens' metaphorically refers to 'production countries'.;
- 'Plucked the golden fruit of greatest revenue' metaphorically refers to earning the highest revenue among films produced in those countries.;
- 'Pinnacle' indicates that these films are at the top in terms of revenue within their countries.;
